'Victor go ahead of them,then draw your bow and fire.'I say.'Not confident in your abilities I see?'he says
provocatively.'Just do it and stop being so painfully irritating.'I respond in annoyance,he smirks then
gallops ahead of the birds.Once ahead he withdraws a bow and an arrow from the quiver fastened to the
saddle on his horse.After the falcons pass above him he draws the arrow aims and shoots,the arrow soars gracefully
and hits the target sending the one of the birds crashing into the ground.
